sql:
SELECT DISTINCT users.username
FROM users
INNER JOIN listening_history ON users.user_id = listening_history.user_id;

SELECT s.title
FROM songs s
WHERE s.song_id = (
    SELECT MAX(sh.song_id)
    FROM listening_history sh
);

external_knowledge:
- 'High-end listeners' refers to users with a 'Premium' account type;
- 'Over the past month' means the last 30 days from the current date;
- The 'favored track' is defined as the song that has been played the most by users fitting the criteria.
